    "created_at": "2014-12-26T17:52:48Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-12-26T17:52:48Z",
    "body": "In the error chaining RFC the return type of `Error::detail` is `Option<&str>`, yet in the implementing PR (#17753), the return type is `Option<String>` and remains this way. I think a string slice is better, as it prevents allocations in the common case where you store an `Option<String>`. I don't have very good internet access at the moment, but I could have a PR up in a few days if you think this change is worthwhile.\n",
