    "created_at": "2014-12-27T22:05:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-12-27T22:05:29Z",
    "body": "@michaelsproul The reason the API was changed was to support another pattern: that you _lazily_ perform the allocation and creation of the string, based on more meaningful fields that are part of the error type. But that does mean you have to create a fresh copy each time.\n\nIt just occurred to me that the best solution might instead be to use the `fmt` infrastructure; I left [a comment on an open RFC](https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/492#issuecomment-68191570) raising this question.\n",
